      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that there's debate but it feels like you're being a bit evasive. like, if you look at the actual text and the history of how the founding fathers viewed militias/self-defense, doesn't one side just have a much stronger, more logical connection to the text? it feels like one side is just relying on historical facts while the other is just trying to adapt it to modern politics. can't you say which one is more legally rigorous?",
