      "content": "The legal rigor of the two sides hinges on which constitutional theory you prioritize, but the modern Supreme Court's rulings have clearly favored a robust interpretation of the Second Amendment. This view emphasizes the text's plain meaning regarding the right to keep and bear arms, viewing the militia clause as supplementary rather than limiting. The argument that the Court is \"making stuff up\" is a political critique, but legally, the current majority has established a strong precedent based on originalist textual analysis.",
